We have photographed elopements in a lot of locations over the years, narrowed down our travel schedule to work in our very favorites, and there is only one âman madeâ place on the list we base our schedule around. Amangiri is a remote luxury resort tucked deep in the white sandstone mesas in southern Utah. Everything about it was designed with the unique desert property in mind, and the details are so thoughtful I often struggle to find the line between epic landscape and beautiful architecture. Weâve become friends with the staff, familiar with the place, and fallen in love with the creativity behind planning and photographing elopements here.
-
So when Mary & Richard reached out to us, we couldnât say yes fast enough. They trusted us with their timeline and plans, and I am so stoked on what we came up with. Mary grew up in Wyoming and most of her favorite memories include the mountains, and they wanted their elopement to be stress-free and flow perfectly into a relaxing honeymoon, so naturally @amangiri was perfect for them. When Mary sent me photos of her fairytale dress with a stunning full-length slit, I knew we had to incorporate horseback riding! This was our first time shooting with horses and it was so much fun! From their peaceful ceremony, gorgeous candlelit dinner, cozy sunrise from their room, and then literally riding off into the desert together at the end, their elopement was so much fun and one we wonât soon forget. I canât wait to share more from this incredible day ð
